/dbpedia.org/resource/Hassanal_Bolkiah_Trophy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hassanal_Bolkiah_Trophy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The bike\", \"from\": 3776, \"to\": 3784}, {\"ngram\": \"use\", \"from\": 3798, \"to\": 3801}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2020 Olympics\", \"from\": 3805, \"to\": 3822}, {\"ngram\": \"seven medals\", \"from\": 3885, \"to\": 3897}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlike the first generation, updates for this year are less radical.\", \"from\": 3900, \"to\": 3968, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first generation\", \"from\": 3907, \"to\": 3927}, {\"ngram\": \"this year\", \"from\": 3941, \"to\": 3950}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As with any rule book, the UCI rules only allow designs to go to a certain point.\", \"from\": 3969, \"to\": 4050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3996, \"end\": 3999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5475113385952494e-17, \"text\": \"UCI\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any rule book\", \"from\": 3977, \"to\": 3990}, {\"ngram\": \"designs\", \"from\": 4017, \"to\": 4024}, {\"ngram\": \"a certain point\", \"from\": 4034, \"to\": 4049}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the first generation benefited from rule changes Pendred shares that the second generation is more about refinement saying, \\\"there will always be room for improvement, albeit with diminishing returns.\\\"\", \"from\": 4051, \"to\": 4258, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first generation\", \"from\": 4057, \"to\": 4077}, {\"ngram\": \"rule changes\", \"from\": 4093, \"to\": 4105}, {\"ngram\": \"Pendred shares\", \"from\": 4106, \"to\": 4120}, {\"ngram\": \"the second generation\", \"from\": 4126, \"to\": 4147}, {\"ngram\": \"refinement\", \"from\": 4162, \"to\": 4172}, {\"ngram\": \"saying\", \"from\": 4173, \"to\": 4179}, {\"ngram\": \"room\", \"from\": 4203, \"to\": 4207}, {\"ngram\": \"improvement\", \"from\": 4212, \"to\": 4223}, {\"ngram\": \"returns\", \"from\": 4249, \"to\": 4256}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To be fair though, he also leaves room for continued improvement going on to say, \\\"as this is still a relatively new concept in bike design there is still a lot to learn and room to develop it further.\\\"\", \"from\": 4259, \"to\": 4461, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"room\", \"from\": 4293, \"to\": 4297}, {\"ngram\": \"continued improvement\", \"from\": 4302, \"to\": 4323}, {\"ngram\": \"a relatively new concept\", \"from\": 4359, \"to\": 4383}, {\"ngram\": \"bike design\", \"from\": 4387, \"to\": 4398}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 4414, \"to\": 4419}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To help make sense of where things are right now in the development, Pendred states \\\"due to COVID delaying the Tokyo games, there has been a shorter time frame to develop the bike so after speaking to British Cycling we worked out the best way to improve the bike and still make it possible to have something faster for the whole team in Paris.\", \"from\": 4463, \"to\": 4807, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4574, \"end\": 4579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9988576551873717, \"rank\": 0.0008743253243212143, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 4664, \"end\": 4679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Cycling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\"}, {\"begin\": 4801, \"end\": 4806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.6565389123414896e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sense\", \"from\": 4476, \"to\": 4481}, {\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 4491, \"to\": 4497}, {\"ngram\": \"the development\", \"from\": 4515, \"to\": 4530}, {\"ngram\": \"a shorter time frame\", \"from\": 4602, \"to\": 4622}, {\"ngram\": \"the bike\", \"from\": 4634, \"to\": 4642}, {\"ngram\": \"the best way\", \"from\": 4694, \"to\": 4706}, {\"ngram\": \"the bike\", \"from\": 4718, \"to\": 4726}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 4762, \"to\": 4771}, {\"ngram\": \"the whole team\", \"from\": 4783, \"to\": 4797}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The front end was the biggest focus and we have designed our frame tooling so we can add/remove different head tube sections therefore allowing a reduced frontal area and also the integration of the stem/bars into the top tube of the frame.\", \"from\": 4808, \"to\": 5048, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The front end\", \"from\": 4808, \"to\": 4821}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest focus\", \"from\": 4826, \"to\": 4843}, {\"ngram\": \"different head tube sections\", \"from\": 4904, \"to\": 4932}, {\"ngram\": \"a reduced frontal area\", \"from\": 4952, \"to\": 4974}, {\"ngram\": \"also the integration\", \"from\": 4979, \"to\": 4999}, {\"ngram\": \"the stem/bars\", \"from\": 5003, \"to\": 5016}, {\"ngram\": \"the top tube\", \"from\": 5022, \"to\": 5034}, {\"ngram\": \"the frame\", \"from\": 5038, \"to\": 5047}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We also redesigned the seat stays for a drag reduction, and combined with new forks and new handlebars it has stacked up to be a significant improvement on the Tokyo frameset.\\\"\", \"from\": 5049, \"to\": 5225, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5209, \"end\": 5214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 